27:41.620 --> 27:43.288
[over intercom]
<i>‐ Hey, it's Clyde.</i>

27:45.332 --> 27:47.125
‐ Uh... what's up?

27:47.751 --> 27:49.837
CLYDE:
<i>Uh, I'm sorry I didn't call.</i>

27:49.837 --> 27:52.214
<i>I think I left my phone in your apartment.</i>

27:52.214 --> 27:54.591
<i>I think it's in the bedroom?</i>

27:57.469 --> 27:59.263
Hey, how's it going?

28:00.097 --> 28:01.557
‐ Here you go.
‐ Oh.

28:02.015 --> 28:03.267
Awesome. Thanks.

28:03.267 --> 28:05.978
‐ Little suckers really get in the way
of sneaking out of places, don't they?

28:06.603 --> 28:07.688
‐ What? No, I didn't‐‐

28:09.273 --> 28:11.400
Okay, I know
that's what this looks like, but‐‐

28:13.402 --> 28:15.153
They towed my car.

28:15.153 --> 28:17.656
‐ Right.
‐ No, no, no, no, no. Look, seriously,

28:17.656 --> 28:19.199
I got up to go to the bathroom

28:19.199 --> 28:21.660
and I look outside,
and they're towing my car.

28:22.661 --> 28:24.454
I literally chased a tow truck

28:25.080 --> 28:27.291
down your street,
and then I had to go to work, so‐‐

28:28.333 --> 28:31.211
I didn't realize I didn't have my phone
until I got on the subway.

28:32.171 --> 28:33.755
And then I couldn't figure out
the subway, so,

28:34.673 --> 28:35.841
that was pretty comical.

28:36.466 --> 28:37.634
‐ Cool story, bro.

28:38.218 --> 28:39.887
‐ Hey. Yo.
‐ Yeah. Yes.

28:40.804 --> 28:42.347
‐ I thought we had a good time.

28:43.599 --> 28:44.600
I‐‐ I really thought‐‐

28:44.600 --> 28:46.810
‐ Yeah. Yeah, we had a good time.
‐ Yeah.

28:49.521 --> 28:50.814
‐ So, can I just

28:51.565 --> 28:53.317
come in and we can, like, talk or‐‐

28:53.775 --> 28:55.903
‐ Yeah, I just‐‐ I don't, I don't think
that's a good idea.

28:55.903 --> 28:57.404
‐ You don't think that's a good idea

28:57.905 --> 29:00.199
or... you know it's not a good idea?

29:00.199 --> 29:02.117
‐ I don't know if I think
it's a good idea.

29:02.117 --> 29:03.118
‐ Okay.
‐ Okay.

29:03.118 --> 29:04.119
‐ All right.

29:04.912 --> 29:05.913
This is for you.

29:07.831 --> 29:09.166
It's French toast.

29:17.549 --> 29:19.176
‐ Okay, so he was a nice guy.

29:20.719 --> 29:21.720
Like,

29:23.514 --> 29:25.682
[sighs]
an actual nice guy.

29:28.352 --> 29:29.436
So,

29:30.938 --> 29:35.567
why did I just act like such a dick?

29:36.818 --> 29:38.570
(Nick Drake's <i>Pink Moon</i> playing)

29:38.570 --> 29:40.781
<i>♪ I saw it written and I saw it say ♪</i>

29:40.781 --> 29:42.658
<i>Maybe there's something</i>
<i>I forgot to mention.</i>

29:42.658 --> 29:43.992
‐ Rob! Rob!
ROB: <i>The other night</i>

29:43.992 --> 29:46.662
<i>before my, um, date with Clyde.</i>

29:46.662 --> 29:47.538
Mac.

29:50.082 --> 29:50.999
Um...

29:50.999 --> 29:52.209
♪ song continues over headphones ♪

29:52.209 --> 29:53.293
What are you doing here?

29:54.461 --> 29:55.963
‐ I moved back a couple of weeks ago.

29:58.048 --> 29:59.299
‐ Like, um,

30:00.175 --> 30:01.426
like, like back‐back?

30:02.761 --> 30:04.221
‐ Yeah, uh...

30:04.221 --> 30:06.515
I was‐‐ I've been meaning to

30:07.307 --> 30:08.559
you know.
‐ Yeah.

30:09.059 --> 30:10.185
Yeah.

30:10.185 --> 30:11.144
‐ Mmm.

30:17.651 --> 30:19.778
So, uh, you still in the neighborhood?

30:21.071 --> 30:22.489
‐ Uh, yeah, yeah.

30:22.948 --> 30:23.991
Got the shop, you know.

30:27.327 --> 30:28.996
Well, we should talk.

30:29.621 --> 30:30.581
Sometime.

30:32.457 --> 30:33.584
I've been, uh‐‐

30:33.584 --> 30:35.919
‐ Ah!
‐ Whoa! Whoa! Dude. Man, what the hell!

30:35.919 --> 30:36.753
‐ Fuck!

30:36.753 --> 30:38.547
‐ You okay.
‐ [Rob grunts]

30:38.547 --> 30:40.048
MAC: You okay?
‐ Shit.

30:40.048 --> 30:40.924
Yeah, I'm fine.

30:40.924 --> 30:42.134
‐ You're bleeding.
‐ I'm fine.

30:42.134 --> 30:44.011
‐ You sure?
‐ Yeah, I'm good. I'm fine.

30:45.012 --> 30:46.013
Um,

30:46.847 --> 30:48.015
I'll‐‐ It's good‐‐

30:49.683 --> 30:51.185
Uh, I'll see you around.

30:52.728 --> 30:54.813
‐ All right. Bye, Rob.

30:55.981 --> 30:57.232
[horn honking]

30:57.232 --> 31:00.652
♪ <i>Pink Moon</i> resumes ♪

31:00.652 --> 31:02.988
<i>♪ I saw it written and I saw it say ♪</i>

31:06.533 --> 31:09.661
<i>♪ Pink moon is on its way ♪</i>

31:11.163 --> 31:14.416
[indiscernible conversations]

31:14.416 --> 31:18.128
Hey, Jeff. Do you have
anything for, um... this?

31:18.128 --> 31:19.505
JEFF: Yeah, sure.

31:24.510 --> 31:26.929
<i>♪ Hey, it's a pink moon ♪</i>

31:28.931 --> 31:30.766
♪ <i>Pink, pink, pink...</i> ♪

31:30.766 --> 31:31.808
‐ Thanks.

31:33.101 --> 31:34.520
[sighs]

31:34.520 --> 31:36.813
[thunder rumbling]

31:36.813 --> 31:38.607
The ugly truth of the matter is this:

31:40.067 --> 31:41.652
if we suddenly heard

31:42.319 --> 31:45.405
that the world was going
to end in 24 hours

31:46.698 --> 31:49.493
people I would call in the first hour
would be the obvious:

31:49.493 --> 31:51.745
my parents, my brother, Simon,

31:51.745 --> 31:52.871
Cherise, I guess.

31:56.667 --> 31:58.126
And I would be calling them all

31:59.378 --> 32:02.172
to apologize for the fact
that I would be choosing

32:02.172 --> 32:03.715
to spend the next

32:05.759 --> 32:07.678
23 hours with

32:08.220 --> 32:09.179
Mac.

32:19.606 --> 32:20.566
Who's back.

32:24.027 --> 32:25.320
It's messed up, I know.

32:29.825 --> 32:31.159
[exhales]

32:48.760 --> 32:50.637
[rain falling]

32:50.637 --> 32:53.307
Thank you, Ann Peebles.

